caption:
At the FIFA Council meeting, it was unanimously agreed that the sole candidacy for the 2030 edition of the FIFA World Cup will be the combined bid of 🇲🇦 Morocco, 🇵🇹 Portugal and 🇪🇸 Spain.

It was also agreed that, as a celebration of the centenary of the FIFA World Cup, 🇺🇾 Uruguay, 🇦🇷 Argentina and 🇵🇾 Paraguay will organise one match each in their respective countries, starting where it all began – at Montevideo’s mythical Estádio Centenário. 

This is the FIFA Council proposal to the FIFA Congress for 2030, with 2034 moving east to Asia and Oceania to ensure appropriate rotation between continents. In a divided world, FIFA and football are uniting! World football has unanimously agreed on something as important as the hosts of the FIFA World Cup, thus setting another example of how dialogue and mutual understanding can result in agreements where everyone wins, in particular fans, players and all the regions of the globe.

Many thanks to all six continental confederations for your commitment to bringing people together through our beautiful game. We can very proudly say that #FootballUnitesTheWorld ⚽🌍🌎❤️

FIFA World Cup  FIFA Football Awards 
It is time for FIFA as the highest authority in football to innovate to give birth to a new award in the FIFA Best Award. 
Golden Foot Award for players 30 years and over & Golden Shoes Award. 
The Golden Foot was won only once by a player aged 30 years and over who had good performances from all statistics on the field. 
Golden Shoes are judged by the player's contribution, goals + assists. 
How can a great player like Messi never get an award from the irrelevant and not credible Golden Foot Award Monaco ?

FIFA needs to respond to these irrelevant and not credible awards by innovating the FIFA Football Award.
 
Hopefully FIFA innovates in the midst of the onslaught of Globe Soccer Dubai doing massive innovation with the aim of begging and claiming that CR7 is the best of GOAT Messi, Maradona and Pele. Their innovation is part of an effort to trick the public and the highest authorities in football.
